I'm having trouble breathing,

303
00:13:15,295 --> 00:13:17,375
- but I guess it's nothing.
- Let's listen.

304
00:13:18,899 --> 00:13:20,698
Take a deep breath.

305
00:13:22,068 --> 00:13:24,251
And another. Feeling any pain?

306
00:13:24,287 --> 00:13:26,254
My chest hurts. I-I feel hot.

307
00:13:26,289 --> 00:13:28,450
- She's having a panic attack!
- That you gave her.

308
00:13:28,474 --> 00:13:29,668
Your sats have dropped.

309
00:13:29,692 --> 00:13:31,025
I'm gonna put you on oxygen

310
00:13:31,060 --> 00:13:34,028
- and admit you for observation.
- You're going to admit her?

311
00:13:34,064 --> 00:13:35,429
You just said she was fine.

312
00:13:35,464 --> 00:13:37,165
I told you something was wrong.

313
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:39,560
Okay, I'm gonna need you
guys to leave the room, please.

314
00:13:42,856 --> 00:13:44,856
Thank you.

315
00:13:46,843 --> 00:13:48,475
All right.

316
00:13:58,438 --> 00:14:00,538
Introduce me to her.

317
00:14:01,541 --> 00:14:02,974
What?

318
00:14:03,009 --> 00:14:05,243
Gemma Lin is
single-handedly responsible

319
00:14:05,278 --> 00:14:07,306
for bringing avant-garde
to streetwear.

320
00:14:07,330 --> 00:14:10,081
There is no one who
can hold a candle to her.

321
00:14:10,116 --> 00:14:12,983
She's an icon.

322
00:14:13,019 --> 00:14:15,853
But I wouldn't expect you
to know anything about that.

323
00:14:15,888 --> 00:14:18,556
What? 'Cause I'm a guy I
don't know about fashion?

324
00:14:18,591 --> 00:14:21,058
You tell me. What are
you wearing tonight?

325
00:14:21,093 --> 00:14:23,695
It's a royal ball. I have a tux.

326
00:14:23,730 --> 00:14:25,896
You have a tux,
or you rented a tux?

327
00:14:28,702 --> 00:14:30,084
I figured.

328
00:14:30,119 --> 00:14:32,853
Introduce me or don't.

329
00:14:32,906 --> 00:14:34,746
I will find a way.

330
00:14:37,744 --> 00:14:39,722
Well, that explains
the abdominal pain.

331
00:14:39,746 --> 00:14:42,041
A mass in her stomach
extending into her small intestine.

332
00:14:42,065 --> 00:14:44,899
Doesn't have the appearance
of a typical stomach cancer.

333
00:14:44,934 --> 00:14:47,952
Regardless, she's gonna need
an endoscopy to biopsy the mass.

334
00:14:49,789 --> 00:14:51,734
Hopefully, I'll have
some answers

335
00:14:51,758 --> 00:14:54,008
for her before I leave.

336
00:14:54,043 --> 00:14:55,843
Don't you mean "we"?

337
00:14:55,878 --> 00:14:57,544
That's surgical.

338
00:14:57,597 --> 00:14:59,731
Gemma's<i> our</i> patient now.

339
00:14:59,766 --> 00:15:02,049
I told you I'd find a way.

340
00:15:06,389 --> 00:15:07,922
How are you feeling?

341
00:15:07,957 --> 00:15:09,874
Better.

342
00:15:09,909 --> 00:15:13,861
I know I seem like the girl
who cried wolf, but, uh...

343
00:15:13,896 --> 00:15:15,863
something feels... wrong.

344
00:15:15,898 --> 00:15:17,414
I believe you.

345
00:15:17,450 --> 00:15:19,228
And we're gonna
figure out what it is.

346
00:15:19,252 --> 00:15:22,219
That's why my dad
doesn't want me in PE.

347
00:15:22,255 --> 00:15:24,049
He says I'm not
like the other kids.

348
00:15:24,073 --> 00:15:25,833
But I want to be. I just...

349
00:15:26,910 --> 00:15:28,721
He means well,

350
00:15:28,745 --> 00:15:32,413
but ever since Mom
died, he's been a little...

351
00:15:32,448 --> 00:15:33,998
overprotective.

352
00:15:34,034 --> 00:15:35,827
- Susan's your stepmom?
- She just wants me

353
00:15:35,851 --> 00:15:37,885
to be independent, mm?

354
00:15:37,920 --> 00:15:40,388
Move out and... and
stand on my own two feet,

355
00:15:40,423 --> 00:15:42,072
and I want that, too.

356
00:15:42,108 --> 00:15:45,175
Could all this just
be my anxiety?

357
00:15:45,211 --> 00:15:47,406
Ah, you'd be surprised

358
00:15:47,430 --> 00:15:50,231
the toll that stress
can take on the body.

359
00:15:50,266 --> 00:15:53,250
Are you feeling
anxious right now?

360
00:15:53,286 --> 00:15:54,819
No. I just...

361
00:15:54,854 --> 00:15:56,987
My legs feel, like...

362
00:15:57,022 --> 00:15:59,539
tingly, like Jell-O.

363
00:16:00,943 --> 00:16:03,422
How about this?
Do you feel this?

364
00:16:03,446 --> 00:16:05,813
I don't feel that at all.

365
00:16:05,848 --> 00:16:07,865
What does that mean?

366
00:16:13,890 --> 00:16:15,851
Dr. Bell. I need to
get new assignments

367
00:16:15,875 --> 00:16:17,257
for some obstetrics residents.

368
00:16:17,293 --> 00:16:20,294
You have room for,
say, two in gen surgery?

369
00:16:22,481 --> 00:16:24,849
Depends. Why are
they leaving OB?

370
00:16:24,884 --> 00:16:27,885
Red Rock is shutting
down the entire department.

371
00:16:29,639 --> 00:16:31,822
You know, I should've
seen this coming.

372
00:16:31,858 --> 00:16:33,836
OB has the highest premiums
and malpractice claims

373
00:16:33,860 --> 00:16:36,193
- of any department.
- Yeah, and new moms can stay

374
00:16:36,228 --> 00:16:38,207
for days without Red
Rock billing a dime.

375
00:16:38,231 --> 00:16:40,964
It's their nightmare.
Maximum care, minimum profit.

376
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:42,511
No, I think this new
neurosurgery center

377
00:16:42,535 --> 00:16:44,968
has them overextended,
and this is just the beginning.

378
00:16:45,004 --> 00:16:47,132
- Well, how about we stop it?
- Well, we-we can't.

379
00:16:47,156 --> 00:16:49,151
No one can. The only thing
that talks in medicine is money.

380
00:16:49,175 --> 00:16:50,869
So unless you
got a whole lot of it

381
00:16:50,893 --> 00:16:52,355
- lying around...
- I know, I know.

382
00:16:52,379 --> 00:16:54,845
Well, maybe we can't
stop it, but what we can do

383
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:56,909
is try and help at least
some of these doctors,

384
00:16:56,933 --> 00:16:59,167
who will lose their
careers if we don't.

385
00:16:59,202 --> 00:17:01,669
Two residents?

386
00:17:01,704 --> 00:17:04,024
- That's all I'm asking.
- Yeah. I'll see what I can do.

387
00:17:05,391 --> 00:17:07,508
Your doctor is going
to a black-tie event,

388
00:17:07,544 --> 00:17:09,343
and I think he needs your help.

389
00:17:09,396 --> 00:17:12,046
He's clueless. You're brilliant.

390
00:17:12,081 --> 00:17:14,682
No, seriously, your fall line
was my favorite collection

391
00:17:14,717 --> 00:17:16,262
of the year.

392
00:17:16,286 --> 00:17:18,318
- I am such a big fan.
- Thank you.

393
00:17:18,354 --> 00:17:19,853
Hey.

394
00:17:19,906 --> 00:17:21,333
Ooh.

395
00:17:21,357 --> 00:17:22,723
No. No, no, no, no, no.

396
00:17:22,758 --> 00:17:24,708
What are you wearing?

397
00:17:24,744 --> 00:17:26,004
What do you mean? It's a tux.

398
00:17:26,028 --> 00:17:27,612
Says who?

399
00:17:27,647 --> 00:17:29,925
Okay, I'm leaving, but I
will be back to check on you

400
00:17:29,949 --> 00:17:32,182
after your endoscopy.

401
00:17:32,218 --> 00:17:34,835
But right now, I have a
princess waiting for me.

402
00:17:34,871 --> 00:17:37,516
- Is she blind?
- Uh, seriously, though,

403
00:17:37,540 --> 00:17:38,790
you can't go looking like that.

404
00:17:39,876 --> 00:17:41,859
I appreciate all your concern,

405
00:17:41,894 --> 00:17:44,273
- but I really don't have
the time to...
- I do.

406
00:17:44,297 --> 00:17:46,758
And I can't, in good conscience,
send you to a party like this.

407
00:17:46,782 --> 00:17:49,783
My team can get you into
something amazing immediately.

408
00:17:55,791 --> 00:17:57,591
Okay. Fine.

409
00:17:57,644 --> 00:18:00,411
What's your chest
measurement? 38?

410
00:18:00,446 --> 00:18:02,880
42, at least.

411
00:18:02,915 --> 00:18:04,916
You're a 38.

412
00:18:10,506 --> 00:18:11,989
Whoa.

413
00:18:12,025 --> 00:18:13,807
Who invited 007?

414
00:18:13,842 --> 00:18:15,921
Well, you better bring your
A game tonight, Hawkins,

415
00:18:15,945 --> 00:18:17,423
'cause I ain't
messing around here.

416
00:18:17,447 --> 00:18:18,823
I can see that.

417
00:18:18,847 --> 00:18:20,047
How did this happen?

418
00:18:20,082 --> 00:18:23,734
My patient is a famous
fashion designer,

419
00:18:23,770 --> 00:18:25,730
and, as it turns out,
part fairy godmother.

420
00:18:25,754 --> 00:18:28,017
And you mix that with Mina's
very aggressive comments

421
00:18:28,041 --> 00:18:30,908
about my rental tux, and voilà.

422
00:18:30,943 --> 00:18:31,892
Yeah.

423
00:18:31,927 --> 00:18:33,410
Well, you look good, man.

424
00:18:42,688 --> 00:18:45,201
- What happened?
- Well, she just got back
from an X-ray.

425
00:18:45,225 --> 00:18:47,353
- I came to take her
for the endoscopy.
- Oh, make it stop.

426
00:18:47,377 --> 00:18:48,820
All right, let's get
four of morphine.

427
00:18:48,844 --> 00:18:49,988
Does it hurt more
when I push my hand in

428
00:18:50,012 --> 00:18:51,924
- or when I take it away?
- When you take it away.

429
00:18:51,948 --> 00:18:53,358
Rebound tenderness. Guarding.

430
00:18:53,382 --> 00:18:55,583
Surgical abdomen.
I'll check the X-rays.

431
00:18:59,072 --> 00:19:00,615
- Air under the diaphragm.
- She's perforated.

432
00:19:00,639 --> 00:19:01,822
Wh-What does that mean?

433
00:19:01,857 --> 00:19:03,052
It means we're
skipping the endoscopy.

434
00:19:03,076 --> 00:19:05,042
You need surgery now. Get Nolan.

435
00:19:05,077 --> 00:19:07,439
- No. No, no, no, no. I can't, I can't go alone.
- Shh. Shh.

436
00:19:07,463 --> 00:19:09,513
- I have no one.
- Shh.

437
00:19:09,548 --> 00:19:12,149
- I'm gonna die alone.
- You're not gonna die, Gemma.

438
00:19:12,185 --> 00:19:14,212
- I will not let that happen.
- Dr. Pravesh,

439
00:19:14,236 --> 00:19:15,636
please stay with me.

440
00:19:15,671 --> 00:19:17,855
I'm so scared.

441
00:19:17,890 --> 00:19:19,306
I'm not gonna leave you.

442
00:19:19,341 --> 00:19:20,841
I promise.

443
00:19:20,877 --> 00:19:22,643
All right? I'm right here.

444
00:19:24,364 --> 00:19:26,797
I got your page.
What do you need?

445
00:19:26,832 --> 00:19:29,244
- Her O2 sats are in the 80s. We need to intubate.
- I can't breathe.

446
00:19:29,268 --> 00:19:31,228
Hey. I need meds
and an airway kit.

447
00:19:31,254 --> 00:19:33,120
Please just help her.

448
00:19:33,155 --> 00:19:35,522
Her paralysis is
progressing rapidly.

449
00:19:35,575 --> 00:19:37,303
She's not gonna be able to
keep breathing on her own.

450
00:19:37,327 --> 00:19:39,487
- What's causing the paralysis?
- We don't know.

451
00:19:40,379 --> 00:19:42,013
Got it.

452
00:19:42,048 --> 00:19:42,963
All right, it's gonna
be okay, Mary.

453
00:19:42,998 --> 00:19:44,909
This is gonna put
you to sleep, all right?

454
00:19:44,933 --> 00:19:46,867
All good.

455
00:19:49,589 --> 00:19:51,316
- Okay, here we go.
- Ready?

456
00:19:51,340 --> 00:19:53,157
Yep.

457
00:19:53,192 --> 00:19:55,153
- Oh, my God.
- You never believed her.

458
00:19:55,177 --> 00:19:57,011
I'm so sorry. I didn't know.

459
00:19:59,799 --> 00:20:01,732
- Got it?
- Got it.

460
00:20:04,203 --> 00:20:07,071
All right, the tube's in.

461
00:20:07,106 --> 00:20:09,067
- She's stable, for now.
- For now?

462
00:20:09,091 --> 00:20:10,902
You-you mean she
could get worse?

463
00:20:10,926 --> 00:20:13,077
Not if we can help it.

464
00:20:15,048 --> 00:20:19,011
I'll begin with an incision
in the gastric fundus.

465
00:20:19,035 --> 00:20:21,018
10-blade.

466
00:20:21,054 --> 00:20:23,365
Got any tips on
crashing a royal ball?

467
00:20:23,389 --> 00:20:25,422
Don't.

468
00:20:28,895 --> 00:20:31,061
Hey. I know. I'm late.

469
00:20:31,096 --> 00:20:32,512
I'm sorry, Nadine.

470
00:20:32,548 --> 00:20:34,715
- My patient needed me.
<i>- I understand.</i>

471
00:20:34,767 --> 00:20:35,882
<i>It's just...</i>

472
00:20:35,935 --> 00:20:38,530
<i>people are starting to arrive.</i>

473
00:20:38,554 --> 00:20:40,031
<i>Traditionally,
you'd be by my side.</i>

474
00:20:40,055 --> 00:20:42,356
I will be there
as soon as I can.

475
00:20:42,391 --> 00:20:44,858
Look, I promise you, this is
a straightforward procedure.

476
00:20:44,893 --> 00:20:49,062
- I'll be out of here in no time.
- What the hell?

477
00:20:51,067 --> 00:20:52,466
Is that...?

478
00:20:52,502 --> 00:20:54,702
A giant,
stomach-shaped hairball.

479
00:20:54,737 --> 00:20:55,920
Nadine, I have to go.

480
00:20:58,908 --> 00:20:59,991
You good?

481
00:21:00,026 --> 00:21:02,209
I think I got hair in my mouth.

482
00:21:02,244 --> 00:21:04,094
I've heard about this before,

483
00:21:04,130 --> 00:21:06,547
but I've never seen such a
severe case of trichophagia.

484
00:21:06,582 --> 00:21:07,914
Gemma's eating her own hair?

485
00:21:07,950 --> 00:21:09,845
That would explain
the no eyebrows.

486
00:21:09,869 --> 00:21:11,829
An obstruction this
big, she's been eating

487
00:21:11,853 --> 00:21:13,603
more than just her eyebrows.

488
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:15,906
And that's not all of it.

489
00:21:15,942 --> 00:21:18,175
There must be a-a tail.

490
00:21:18,210 --> 00:21:21,912
Extends from the gastric
body, beyond the pylorus,

491
00:21:21,948 --> 00:21:23,730
into the duodenum.

492
00:21:23,766 --> 00:21:26,133
- It's Rapunzel syndrome.
- Yeah, it appears so.

493
00:21:26,168 --> 00:21:30,086
We have to untangle the
hair that has wound itself

494
00:21:30,122 --> 00:21:31,666
through the
intestines to extract it.

495
00:21:31,690 --> 00:21:34,759
Yes, repairing whatever
damage we need to along the way.

496
00:21:34,794 --> 00:21:37,411
Sounds complex.

497
00:21:37,446 --> 00:21:40,364
You should call your
princess and let her know.

498
00:21:40,399 --> 00:21:41,782
This is gonna take a while.

499
00:21:47,139 --> 00:21:50,173
Sinus bradycardia
with increasing pauses,

500
00:21:50,209 --> 00:21:51,158
up to five seconds.

501
00:21:51,193 --> 00:21:52,604
Labs are pristine.

502
00:21:52,628 --> 00:21:54,172
The spinal tap
came back negative.

503
00:21:54,196 --> 00:21:55,846
Nothing on imaging.

504
00:21:55,882 --> 00:21:58,098
But her paralysis
is moving so fast.

505
00:21:58,134 --> 00:21:59,817
